notes: Two hand turn to necklace to close position is pretty nice.
The tension from the break is fun.  In the two hand turn, the hands don't need to be close together overhead.
Alternate Crossbody lead. Change of place with left turn.  Use an open break to initiate change of place.
Fun to mix this up with change of place.

Right to right handhold. Can do this at open break.  Open break to initiate hammerlock. Gives her room to wind in.  Hold hammerlock with left hand finger tips. Shoulder left turn on 123, w opposite prep.  Place her left hand on my neck and initiate one handed Crossbody lead.
A CBL lead with the left hand only reaching across.  And then signaling a quick term at the last moment, bringing left hand across her face to her right shoulder to do so.
Left head hold.  Left turn for her like change of place.  Then left turn for him with her hand tracing waist, regripping with his left hand again.
CBL holding with his left hand only.  Draw her hand to my chest on three as a prep before going the other way into the right turns.  Feels like two turns. But it's more like one and a half.
Looks like you step out to the rail on three.

Open break  Get out of her way! ... on the left rail. (opposite of CBL) Don't make her leave the slot!  Keep left-hand through the turn  Don't get too far apart. Don't need too much tension after open break.
Ope break and toss w left hand to intimate checks.
right handover grip  right half turn  his right forearm lance on her shoulder  shadow past basics  can go to copa position
No need to catch her firmly. Can catch her gently and send her back.
Simply cross body lead with him doing a left turn, tracing her hand on his hips, and catching it again
Titanic seems to refer to copa position, arms wide shadow position
Closed position CBL.  Release lt hand, open break, step out of slot, left turn as she passes, straight back to closed position.
Closed position CBL  Catch rt-rt hand, open break, Enchufa, catch arm to rt turn as she passes  Place her right hand in her left, closed position, CBL

Closed position CBL  Cross hands, right over, rt turn to hammerlock  Hairbrush w right hand, to CBL w left turn to unwind  Catch torso w right hand, bring her rt hand his head w left, straight back into CBL  ... But then catch her again, and send her into rt turn the other way

Closed position, CBL  Cross to right hand hold & open break  Start rev CBL w rt hand high, grab w left under before she passes  Quick turn w two hand over head, into sombrero for both  Then CBL w early shoulder left turn (reach across w left)  Catch the turn as she turns away, gently puller her back on 5-6-7 for 1.5 rt turn into closed position
Rt two hand, cuddle, out the back, CBL inside, duck reverse CBL to closed
